1
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:11,800
Monou?

2
00:00:13,850 --> 00:00:15,890
Hirose.

3
00:00:22,530 --> 00:00:24,360
This is...

4
00:00:28,270 --> 00:00:30,680
One of my buildings.

5
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:32,860
Have you been visiting them all?

6
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:35,350
Yes.

7
00:00:36,060 --> 00:00:38,500
I cannot decide what to do for our project.

8
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:40,570
So, I thought visiting your works

9
00:00:40,570 --> 00:00:44,910
would give me the idea I need.

10
00:00:44,910 --> 00:00:46,720
I see.

11
00:00:48,060 --> 00:00:51,600
I didn't think you'd catch me in action.

12
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:53,640
How embarrassing...

13
00:00:54,410 --> 00:00:56,800
Don't be embarrassed.

14
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:59,690
It shows your passion for this project.

15
00:00:59,690 --> 00:01:01,580
I'm happy you wish to work with me.

16
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:05,050
I will do my best to impress.

17
00:01:06,070 --> 00:01:08,260
I promise to bring

18
00:01:08,260 --> 00:01:11,210
a proposal that piques your interest.

19
00:01:11,210 --> 00:01:13,230
Good night.

20
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:16,070
Monou.

21
00:01:17,020 --> 00:01:18,640
Yes?

22
00:01:19,570 --> 00:01:21,170
Did you have any plans

23
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:25,100
for the evening?

24
00:01:26,350 --> 00:01:29,570
Tonight?

25
00:01:29,570 --> 00:01:31,090
Yes.

26
00:01:32,020 --> 00:01:36,510
If you're free,
would you like to join me for dinner?

27
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:40,050
What?

28
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:48,090
This building feels
completely different on the inside.

29
00:02:48,090 --> 00:02:50,610
I will be taking notes.

30
00:02:50,610 --> 00:02:51,600
Thank you.

31
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:53,200
Thank you.

32
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:55,710
Cheers.

33
00:02:55,710 --> 00:02:57,410
Cheers.

34
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:10,030
I should have asked this before,

35
00:03:10,030 --> 00:03:14,660
but am I pulling you away from work?

36
00:03:14,660 --> 00:03:19,080
Not at all. I appreciate any opportunity

37
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:21,240
to glean anything new from you.

38
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:24,000
Anything new, is it?

39
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:29,780
I can certainly offer you
a sorry tale, at least.

40
00:03:34,870 --> 00:03:40,060
Truth be told,
I didn't wish to eat alone tonight.

41
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:42,860
You have those sorts of days as well?

42
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:44,880
Of course.

43
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:50,880
If there's something
on your mind, I'll listen.

44
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:52,830
Thank you.

45
00:03:56,710 --> 00:04:03,280
My former wife has just remarried.

46
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:07,640
She will be having a child next spring.
[Just Married]

47
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:12,040
I see.

48
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:13,520
Yes.

49
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:19,070
We mutually agreed to part ways,

50
00:04:19,070 --> 00:04:22,230
but when I hear of her new partner,

51
00:04:22,230 --> 00:04:24,610
I can't help but feel conflicted.

52
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:28,570
See? It's a sorry tale, right?

53
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:32,460
I don't think so.

54
00:04:32,460 --> 00:04:34,910
What you're feeling is entirely valid.

55
00:04:37,540 --> 00:04:39,590
Thank you.

56
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:44,350
I had read previously in an interview

57
00:04:44,350 --> 00:04:47,890
that you started the company with your wife?

58
00:04:51,170 --> 00:04:53,040
Yes.

59
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:56,650
<i>And I assumed we would be partners for life.</i>

60
00:04:59,180 --> 00:05:01,980
You want a child?

61
00:05:04,540 --> 00:05:06,980
Why now, after all this time?

62
00:05:06,980 --> 00:05:11,800
People change.

63
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:22,070
I can't make your wish come true.

64
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:25,450
Why?

65
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:28,380
Dear...

66
00:05:30,550 --> 00:05:33,780
You don't think to change?

67
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:40,560
I'm sorry.

68
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,380
<i>When we first met,</i>

69
00:05:42,380 --> 00:05:47,750
she wanted to prioritize her career,
and had no desire for children.

70
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:49,840
And yet...

71
00:05:53,710 --> 00:06:00,550
You've never wanted a child yourself?

72
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:04,460
I am the third son of a temple.

73
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,240
Oh...

74
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:11,020
Surprised?

75
00:06:11,020 --> 00:06:12,560
Yes, very.

76
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:15,630
That is the reaction I often receive.

77
00:06:19,310 --> 00:06:24,460
Although my older brother
took up the family mantle,

78
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:29,580
he was always pressured to have an heir.

79
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,850
As a result,

80
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:36,820
I decided I wanted no children in my life.

81
00:06:39,710 --> 00:06:42,180
I see.

82
00:06:43,870 --> 00:06:48,090
Life never quite works out
as planned, does it?

83
00:06:51,970 --> 00:06:54,590
It certainly doesn't.

84
00:06:57,980 --> 00:07:00,750
Still, the divorce wasn't inherently
a bad experience.

85
00:07:01,610 --> 00:07:04,360
It radicalized my beliefs

86
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:09,750
on what makes a home.

87
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:14,350
"What makes a home"...

88
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:18,510
After my divorce,

89
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:21,950
I wished to create homes
that were free of prejudice.

90
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:25,910
Homes, not bound by the idea

91
00:07:25,910 --> 00:07:30,320
of the nuclear family.

92
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:46,750
Morning.

93
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,430
Morning.

94
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:55,050
<i>Your door is now locked.</i>

95
00:08:09,290 --> 00:08:11,070
<i>Those two</i>

96
00:08:11,070 --> 00:08:13,870
<i>are a couple now.</i>

97
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:21,000
Am I walking too fast?

98
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,460
Huh?

99
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:26,650
No, not at all.

100
00:08:30,130 --> 00:08:34,120
But you're dating Mizuno now.

101
00:08:35,570 --> 00:08:37,050
What?

102
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:42,450
I wouldn't want to cause
any misunderstandings.

103
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:47,730
No, well...

104
00:08:47,730 --> 00:08:49,780
Good morning.

105
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:58,880
Good morning.

106
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:11,670
Here, I bought us some tumblers.

107
00:09:11,670 --> 00:09:13,400
Oh...

108
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,160
Thanks.

109
00:09:16,020 --> 00:09:18,910
Let me treat you to breakfast.

110
00:09:18,910 --> 00:09:20,960
Really? I'd love that.

111
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:23,990
Would you like to join us, Monou?

112
00:09:23,990 --> 00:09:27,690
Thank you,
but I'll go on ahead to the office.

113
00:09:27,690 --> 00:09:29,970
Okay, we'll see you there.

114
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:34,060
They're matching.

115
00:09:34,060 --> 00:09:36,860
I see. This is my first tumbler.

116
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:38,640
It is really?

117
00:09:44,470 --> 00:09:47,640
Is your proposal due next week?

118
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:49,120
Yes, next Friday.

119
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:51,850
Let me know if I can help.

120
00:09:51,850 --> 00:09:54,000
Thank you.

121
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:04,250
Hirose's wife works as his secretary, right?

122
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:07,930
What an absolute power couple.

123
00:10:07,930 --> 00:10:11,980
Actually, she's no longer at the company.

124
00:10:12,810 --> 00:10:14,260
What?

125
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:23,040
Did they get a divorce?

126
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,480
Yes.

127
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:29,380
But they were perfect for each other.

128
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:34,010
Hirose said it was a good experience for him.

129
00:10:34,010 --> 00:10:36,410
He didn't seem too down about it.

130
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:40,600
Did you know, Mao?

131
00:10:41,770 --> 00:10:43,340
No.

132
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:55,860
Hirose works as his own secretary now.

133
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:07,810
Nana, want any coffee? I can go brew some.

134
00:11:08,890 --> 00:11:11,650
No thank you. I have a cup already.

135
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,020
I see.

136
00:11:14,020 --> 00:11:16,080
What about you, Monou?

137
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,980
I'll be fine as well.

138
00:11:17,980 --> 00:11:22,520
Then I'll just get some for myself.

139
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:26,040
[Idea Construction Office]

140
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:36,990
Heading out?

141
00:11:36,990 --> 00:11:40,570
Yeah. I have a visit with Sanou Systems.

142
00:11:42,630 --> 00:11:44,270
Mao.

143
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:49,800
Promise you won't make Nana cry again.

144
00:11:51,820 --> 00:11:53,270
Huh?

145
00:11:53,970 --> 00:11:57,550
You know she's a fragile girl.

146
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:59,850
If you hurt her again,

147
00:11:59,850 --> 00:12:01,960
- I'll...
- I promise.

148
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:11,040
I'm really sorry about the other night.

149
00:12:14,370 --> 00:12:16,400
As long as you get it.

150
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,000
See you later.

151
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:38,400
Sui, you said you'd visit often.

152
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,940
Sorry, sorry.

153
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:44,100
I have an important deadline
coming up next week.

154
00:12:44,810 --> 00:12:47,500
Then I won't rag on you, for now.

155
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:50,610
What's the deadline for?

156
00:12:50,610 --> 00:12:53,790
We'll be inviting an architect
named Takaomi Hirose

157
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:55,930
to hold a public talk with our boss.

158
00:12:55,930 --> 00:12:58,520
I'm supposed to come up
with the topics they'll discuss.

159
00:13:01,340 --> 00:13:04,690
My first proposal was already shot down.

160
00:13:04,690 --> 00:13:08,400
What, is this Hirose guy a stingy dude?

161
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,700
Not at all. In fact, the very opposite.

162
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:12,830
He's a sincere gentleman

163
00:13:12,830 --> 00:13:15,420
who listens to what I have to say,

164
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:18,030
and even gives me advice.

165
00:13:18,030 --> 00:13:21,890
I can tell he's passionate about his work.

166
00:13:21,890 --> 00:13:24,910
Are you sure he's not just interested in you?

167
00:13:24,910 --> 00:13:26,400
Huh?

168
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:29,530
Ignore me.

169
00:13:29,530 --> 00:13:32,650
Glad he's such a nice guy.

170
00:13:34,990 --> 00:13:38,900
I hope your next proposal goes well.

171
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:40,770
Thanks.

172
00:13:40,770 --> 00:13:42,250
- Here.
- Thanks.

173
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:50,190
My famous fried chicken
is sure to keep you going.

174
00:13:50,190 --> 00:13:52,290
I guarentee it.

175
00:13:52,290 --> 00:13:55,890
I can't believe you're the one
cooking for us.

176
00:13:55,890 --> 00:13:57,810
Your big sis is proud.

177
00:13:58,970 --> 00:14:01,730
Thanks for taking care of the food back then.

178
00:14:01,730 --> 00:14:03,340
Of course.

179
00:14:05,030 --> 00:14:07,720
Oh, right. Take this with you, Sui.

180
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:11,230
Found it.

181
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:14,910
Here.

182
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:18,400
What's all this?

183
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:21,490
Miso from our neighbors, the Sasaki's.

184
00:14:21,490 --> 00:14:23,570
I set aside a share for you.

185
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:25,720
Thanks.

186
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:29,720
Aren't the Sasaki's moving out soon?

187
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:32,020
Yeah, they'll be leaving next week.

188
00:14:32,020 --> 00:14:37,090
An elderly couple bought the place.

189
00:14:37,090 --> 00:14:41,550
I'm surprised they chose a family home,
for just the two of them.

190
00:14:42,690 --> 00:14:45,110
Just the two of them...

191
00:14:45,110 --> 00:14:47,470
It's a bit large for a retirement home,
don't you think?

192
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:50,090
It is a 4LDK.

193
00:14:50,090 --> 00:14:55,550
Though supposedly
they plan to renovate the place.

194
00:14:55,550 --> 00:14:58,750
But won't they find the space unmanageable?

195
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:02,000
<i>Homes, not bound by the idea</i>

196
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:06,310
<i>of the nuclear family.</i>

197
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:12,680
Rin, thanks.

198
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:14,820
I have to get home.

199
00:15:14,820 --> 00:15:17,850
Huh? Sui?

200
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:21,960
Your miso! Take the miso!

201
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:32,080
What a wonderful catalogue.

202
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:34,610
This is no longer in print, isn't it?

203
00:15:36,340 --> 00:15:39,190
Yeah, I bought it while on vacation.

204
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,940
I think you'd like this one better.

205
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:49,410
These palettes are more your style, right?

206
00:15:53,270 --> 00:15:54,950
Sorry, was I wrong?

207
00:15:56,940 --> 00:15:59,400
No.

208
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,700
I'm just so happy.

209
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:03,200
Huh?

210
00:16:03,990 --> 00:16:08,860
You know what colors I like.

211
00:16:09,830 --> 00:16:13,320
I was happy when you said yes to dating,

212
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:17,960
but I was worried I was forcing you, so...

213
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:22,410
What? You didn't...

214
00:16:23,290 --> 00:16:24,740
No.

215
00:16:29,060 --> 00:16:32,810
I'm sorry I made you worry.

216
00:16:36,250 --> 00:16:37,890
Mizuno.

217
00:16:41,510 --> 00:16:45,660
Let me protect you. This time, I swear it.

218
00:16:49,950 --> 00:16:52,150
[Good Design Cafe]

219
00:16:58,220 --> 00:17:00,070
Are you all right?

220
00:17:00,890 --> 00:17:03,070
Yes, thank you.

221
00:17:26,810 --> 00:17:30,660
Welcome home.

222
00:17:30,660 --> 00:17:32,520
Thank you.

223
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:34,390
Good night.

224
00:17:38,510 --> 00:17:39,860
Are you all right?

225
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:41,770
Thank you.

226
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:45,800
You seem to be in a hurry.

227
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:49,420
I had a great idea
for our proposal to Hirose.

228
00:17:50,580 --> 00:17:54,360
I have to jot it down before I forget.

229
00:17:54,360 --> 00:17:56,220
You're losing your cool.

230
00:17:56,220 --> 00:17:58,060
Yeah, I know.

231
00:17:58,060 --> 00:18:00,360
But I'm really motivated right now.

232
00:18:01,820 --> 00:18:04,650
Want me to help later?

233
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:08,410
No, I'd like to do this on my own.

234
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:13,420
Good luck.

235
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:15,000
Thank you.

236
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,970
Let's not bother her anymore.

237
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:19,670
- Right.
- See you both tomorrow.

238
00:18:23,840 --> 00:18:26,160
<i>Your door is now unlocked.</i>

239
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:32,100
- Take care.
- Good night.

240
00:19:32,100 --> 00:19:34,160
Good night.

241
00:19:57,740 --> 00:20:01,940
This is the topic I'd like to propose.

242
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:04,860
"An atmosphere, to support your lifestyle".

243
00:20:05,620 --> 00:20:09,140
The other day, you had mentioned to me

244
00:20:09,140 --> 00:20:12,790
how you wished to create homes
that were free of prejudice.

245
00:20:12,790 --> 00:20:14,350
That I did.

246
00:20:14,350 --> 00:20:19,330
Mr. Hoshina also wishes to tackle
a similar philosophy.

247
00:20:19,330 --> 00:20:21,450
Interesting.

248
00:20:21,450 --> 00:20:23,340
Although, in Mr. Hoshina's case,

249
00:20:23,340 --> 00:20:27,050
his interest is in shared homes
for those of different backgrounds.

250
00:20:28,350 --> 00:20:31,800
A place where people
of all ages and genders can reside,

251
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:36,300
rather than living communities,
exclusive to seniors.

252
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,850
I see.

253
00:20:37,850 --> 00:20:40,270
Encouraging many generations to interact

254
00:20:40,270 --> 00:20:44,140
would inspire a youthful spirit
in all residents.

255
00:20:44,140 --> 00:20:46,200
That sounds like a wonderful idea.

256
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:48,860
On that note.

257
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:53,260
I wanted to bring up this residence.

258
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:56,690
This is...

259
00:20:56,690 --> 00:21:01,660
A home for a single lady in her forties, yes?

260
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:05,680
I'm surprised you found this one,
it's quite a ways away.

261
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:11,310
Normally, a large property like this
would be for a family,

262
00:21:11,310 --> 00:21:15,490
especially one with small children.

263
00:21:15,490 --> 00:21:16,990
That is true.

264
00:21:17,570 --> 00:21:20,840
But she requested a home
where she could live in leisure.

265
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:23,340
That was my client's vision.

266
00:21:23,340 --> 00:21:27,610
So, I ignored my preconception
of a single woman's residence,

267
00:21:27,610 --> 00:21:31,130
and designed a home from the ground up.

268
00:21:32,780 --> 00:21:38,650
That philosophy of yours saved me.

269
00:21:38,650 --> 00:21:41,560
I saved you?

270
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,500
Yes.

271
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:46,790
Though this may be a bit personal,

272
00:21:46,790 --> 00:21:53,710
I was recently diagnosed as infertile.

273
00:21:55,710 --> 00:22:00,060
Not every family
can be blessed with children.

274
00:22:00,060 --> 00:22:05,260
Yet, most model rooms
are furnished with a family in mind.

275
00:22:05,260 --> 00:22:09,220
Seeing these deeply hurt me at a point.

276
00:22:10,450 --> 00:22:14,030
But the homes you imagine

277
00:22:14,030 --> 00:22:16,880
are free and liberating.

278
00:22:16,880 --> 00:22:20,160
You aren't bound by the idea of a "family."

279
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:23,710
You treasure many different walks of life.

280
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:26,120
It has fundamentally changed how I think.

281
00:22:28,740 --> 00:22:30,680
Monou.

282
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:35,660
That is the very reason I am an architect.

283
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:37,890
What?

284
00:22:40,180 --> 00:22:41,770
Thank you.

285
00:22:42,430 --> 00:22:44,490
I have never felt more glad

286
00:22:44,490 --> 00:22:46,840
to have pursued architecture as my career.

287
00:22:46,840 --> 00:22:50,900
But I am the one thanking you.

288
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:58,430
Monou.

289
00:22:58,430 --> 00:23:01,970
I will gladly participate in this talk event.

290
00:23:02,970 --> 00:23:05,080
Then...

291
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:07,160
I look forward to working with you.

292
00:23:08,060 --> 00:23:10,240
Thank you.

293
00:23:11,740 --> 00:23:15,560
May we discuss scheduling now?

294
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:17,130
Of course.

295
00:23:18,590 --> 00:23:21,070
I have brought your coffees.

296
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:22,870
Thank you.

297
00:23:30,980 --> 00:23:34,360
["Long time no see."]

298
00:23:45,770 --> 00:23:48,620
I never imagined we'd reunite so quickly.

299
00:23:48,620 --> 00:23:51,730
Listen to your heart already.

300
00:23:51,730 --> 00:23:52,940
Everything all right?

301
00:23:52,940 --> 00:23:55,260
I want to chip away at this alone
for a little longer.

302
00:23:55,260 --> 00:23:57,340
Blame your faulty body.

303
00:23:57,340 --> 00:24:00,000
Let yourself be miserable, damn it!

